verbose_text: First, lever and drug effects at just the S+ and S- levels together (excluding the inactive lever) was separately analyzed using a mixed ANOVA to test for evidence of secondary reward above and beyond sensory reward, but neither a reliable interaction nor a lever effect was observed (Fs < 1, MSe = 2109), although a clear effect of drug was detected [F (1, 30) = 24.40, MSe = 4165, p < 0.0125].
